#
# Let's visualize the highest airports in the world using PySheets and gen AI.
#
# We load a CSV with 80,881 rows containing all aita-registered airports in the world.
# In the next steps, we will add latitude and longitude columns to the dataframe.
# Then we filter for the airports above 14,000 feet.
# Finally, we visualize as a barchart (less useful) and a map (more useful).
#
url = "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/datasets/airport-codes/master/data/airport-codes.csv"

# Load the CSV and convert it into a Pandas DataFrame
pysheets.load_sheet(url)
